President Obama has signed an emergency disaster declaration for the Commonwealth of Massachusetts following a water main break. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate relief efforts and provide assistance to the affected areas. FEMA is authorized to mobilize resources and equipment to alleviate the impact of the emergency. The federal funding for emergency protective measures will be provided at 75 percent. James N. Russo has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. For more information, contact FEMA.